  <item>
    <title>Scarleteen Mix #6:  Consenting and Other Sexual Communication</title>
    <link>https://www.scarleteen.com/zh-hans/blog/heather_corinna/scarleteen_mix_6_consenting_and_other_sexual_communication</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; itemprop=&quot;description&quot;&gt; &lt;p&gt;Real-deal &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.scarleteen.com/zh-hans/glossary#consent&quot; title=&quot;To agree to do something or give permission. In the context of sex, a person is giving full consent/is consenting when they freely and actively agree to do something sexual with someone else; however, the person still has the right to change their mind at any point. A person is NOT consenting if they do not actively agree, have been forced or pressured in some way or are in a state where they are incapable of full consent (such as when asleep, under the influence of drugs or alcohol, or below the age of consent).
&quot; class=&quot;lexicon-term&quot;&gt;consent&lt;/a&gt; requires clear, open and honest &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.scarleteen.com/zh-hans/glossary#communication&quot; title=&quot;Various ways we express and share feelings or thoughts, such as through speech, written words or symbols, sign language, body language, touch or art.&quot; class=&quot;lexicon-term&quot;&gt;communication&lt;/a&gt;. And if we&#039;re going ahead and actually being &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.scarleteen.com/zh-hans/glossary#sexual&quot; title=&quot;About or relating in some way to sex or sexuality.&quot; class=&quot;lexicon-term&quot;&gt;sexual&lt;/a&gt; together in some way,  that also means an ongoing, nuanced and pretty highly situational process of communication, not just one or two super-quick, super-basic exchanges.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not only is communication as a process essential to keeping it consensual, it&#039;s a big part of &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scarleteen.com/glossary#sex&quot; title=&quot;Different things people choose to do to actively express or enact sexuality and sexual feelings; often this involves genitals, but not always. The word sex also means a way people, animals or plants are classified based on their chromosomes, genitals or reproductive organs.&quot;&gt;sex&lt;/a&gt; actually being any &lt;em&gt;good &lt;/em&gt;for everyone involved.&lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;meta  itemprop=&quot;name&quot; content=&quot;Scarleteen Mix #6:  Consenting and Other Sexual Communication&quot; id=&quot;md11&quot; /&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-taxonomy-vocabulary-3 field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/zh-hans/tags/scarleteen_mix&quot;&gt;Scarleteen Mix&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/zh-hans/tags/mixtapes&quot;&gt;mixtapes&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/zh-hans/tags/consent&quot;&gt;consent&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/zh-hans/tags/communication&quot;&gt;communication&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/zh-hans/tags/talking&quot;&gt;talking&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/zh-hans/tags/asking&quot;&gt;asking&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/zh-hans/tags/telling&quot;&gt;telling&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/zh-hans/tags/want&quot;&gt;want&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/zh-hans/tags/dont&quot;&gt;don&amp;#039;t&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/zh-hans/tags/no&quot;&gt;no&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/zh-hans/tags/yes&quot;&gt;yes&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/zh-hans/tags/maybe&quot;&gt;maybe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/zh-hans/tags/sexual&quot;&gt;sexual&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/zh-hans/tags/healthy&quot;&gt;healthy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/zh-hans/tags/abuse&quot;&gt;abuse&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/zh-hans/tags/assault&quot;&gt;assault&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
